<title>SWITZERLAND: Swiss short-time work rose in October.</title>
<headline>Swiss short-time work rose in October.</headline>
<dateline>BERNE 1996-12-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>The number of people affected by short-term working in Switzerland rose to 12,332 in October, up 2,982 from the previous month, the Federal Office for Industry, Trade and Labour said.</p>
<p>The number of work hours lost to short-time working rose by 230,122 to 694,692. The number of companies affected was 169 higher at 919.</p>
<p>In October last year, 501,467 hours were lost, affecting 9,321 workers in 906 firms.</p>
<p>-- Zurich Editorial +41 1 631 7340</p>
